The paper deals with a graph coloring problem motivated by wireless network channel assignment, which suggests a connection to networking and information theory (cs.NI, cs.IT). The problem is NP-hard and has been well-studied from the point of view of approximation, indicating a possible connection to algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). The paper also discusses fixed-parameter tractable algorithms and linear vertex kernels, which are techniques commonly used in parameterized complexity (cs.DM). Finally, the problem involves edge coloring, which is a subfield of graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT).
